@startuml seq-process-memos
title Sequence — /livespec-impl-*:process-memos (with all four dispositions)
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam BackgroundColor white
skinparam ArrowColor #111
skinparam sequence {
  ParticipantBorderColor #111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor white
  ParticipantFontColor #111
  ActorBorderColor #111
  ActorBackgroundColor white
  ActorFontColor #111
  LifeLineBorderColor #444
}

actor "Human user" as User
actor "Agent" as Agent #LightSkyBlue
participant "/livespec:doctor" as Doctor #LightYellow
participant "/livespec-impl-*:\nprocess-memos" as Process #LightYellow
participant "memo store\n(impl backend)" as Memos
participant "/livespec:propose-changes" as Propose #LightYellow
participant "work-item queue" as Queue
participant ".ai/<topic>.md\n+ AGENTS.md" as AiFiles

== Hygiene trigger (background invariant) ==

User -> Doctor : invoke (routine check\nor pre/post wrapper step)
Doctor -> Memos : list-memos --untriaged --json
Memos --> Doctor : N untriaged entries
Doctor -> User : warn: "N memos pending,\nrun process-memos"

== Per-memo dispositions ==

User -> Agent : "run process-memos"
Agent -> Process : invoke
activate Process

Process -> Memos : list-memos --untriaged --json
Memos --> Process : untriaged memo list

loop for each untriaged memo
  Process -> Agent : surface memo text + suggested classification
  Agent -> User : ask: spec-bound / impl-bound /\npersistent-knowledge / discard?

  alt SPEC-BOUND
    User --> Agent : confirms spec-bound
    Agent -> Propose : invoke with memo text as input
    Propose -> Propose : interactive structured authoring
    Propose --> Agent : proposed_change file written
    Agent -> Process : disposition done
    Process -> Memos : mark memo processed
  else IMPL-BOUND
    User --> Agent : confirms impl-bound
    Agent -> Process : disposition
    Process -> Queue : file work item with memo text\n(no gap-id label — freeform)
    Queue --> Process : work item id
    Process -> Memos : mark memo processed
    note right : This work item joins the\nsame queue capture-spec-gaps\npopulates; /livespec-impl-*:\nimplement picks it up later.
  else PERSISTENT-KNOWLEDGE
    User --> Agent : confirms; chooses topic name
    Agent -> AiFiles : write .ai/<topic>.md\nwith memo content
    Agent -> AiFiles : update AGENTS.md\n(and optionally CLAUDE.md)\nwith progressive-load reference
    AiFiles --> Agent : files written
    Process -> Memos : mark memo processed
    note right : Persistent-knowledge is the\nslot for content that doesn't\nrise to spec or impl work\nbut must be reachable by\nfuture agents.
  else DISCARD
    User --> Agent : confirms discard
    Process -> Memos : delete memo
  end
end

Process --> Agent : summary (N processed,\nbreakdown by disposition)
Agent --> User : report
deactivate Process

note over User, AiFiles : Note: livespec-core's doctor\nKNOWS that memos exist (via the\nuntriaged-query contract) but\nNEVER routes them. Routing is\n100% on the impl-plugin side.\nThe only cross-namespace handoff\nis the SPEC-BOUND disposition\ncalling /livespec:propose-changes.

@enduml
